{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-719-Enabling-Your-App-for-CarPlay"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC17","title":"Enabling Your App for CarPlay"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions"},{"style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-213-CarPlay-Audio-and-Navigation-Apps","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-717-Developing-Wireless-CarPlay-Systems","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-722-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-1","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-723-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-2"],"type":"links"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-719-enabling-your-app-for-carplay"]}],"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/719","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (27 min)"}},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand how to enable your audio, messaging, VoIP calling or automaker app for CarPlay. Audio, messaging and VoIP calling apps use a consistent design that’s optimized for use in the car. Automaker apps provide vehicle specific controls and displays to keep drivers connected without leaving CarPlay. Explore best practices and learn about the tools and frameworks for CarPlay apps."}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-723-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-2":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-723-developing-carplay-systems-part-2","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-723-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-2","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Developing CarPlay Systems, Part 2","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how CarPlay integrates with your car’s infotainment system. Understand how CarPlay is designed to work with your car’s resources including the display, speakers, microphone, user inputs, steering wheel controls, instrument cluster and sensors."}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Learn More…","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"title":"WWDC17","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-722-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-1":{"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Developing CarPlay Systems, Part 1","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-722-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-1","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-722-developing-carplay-systems-part-1","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"CarPlay is a smarter, safer way to use your iPhone in the car. Learn how CarPlay works and how to design your car’s infotainment system to work seamlessly with iPhone. Understand best practices for a great user experience that integrates CarPlay with the car’s native system."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-717-Developing-Wireless-CarPlay-Systems":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-717-developing-wireless-carplay-systems","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-717-Developing-Wireless-CarPlay-Systems","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Developing Wireless CarPlay Systems","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Wireless CarPlay is perfect for any trip. Get in your car without taking your iPhone out of your bag or pocket, and start experiencing CarPlay effortlessly. Learn how to design your CarPlay system to connect wirelessly to iPhone. Understand hardware requirements, best practices for a great user experience, and how to optimize the pairing and reconnection process."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2017/719":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/719","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/719","type":"download","checksum":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-213-CarPlay-Audio-and-Navigation-Apps":{"type":"topic","title":"CarPlay Audio and Navigation Apps","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-213-carplay-audio-and-navigation-apps","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-213-CarPlay-Audio-and-Navigation-Apps","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to update your audio or navigation app to support CarPlay. Apps in CarPlay are optimized for use in the car, and automatically adapt to available vehicle screens and input controls. Audio apps can deliver music, news, podcasts, and more. With the new CarPlay framework, Navigation apps can provide detailed maps, destination search, turn-by-turn guidance, and user notifications."}],"kind":"article"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"}}}